name: practice
trans: something that is usually or regularly done, often as a habit, tradition, or custom

name: volunteer
trans: to do something, esp. for other people or for an organization, willingly and without being forced or paid to do it

name: delicate
trans: needing careful treatment, esp. because easily damaged

name: Concept
trans: a principle or idea

name: publicity
trans: the activity of making certain that someone or something attracts a lot of interest or attention from many people, or the attention received as a result of this activity

name: injure
trans: to hurt a living creature, esp. to cause physical harm to someone

name: strive
trans: to try hard to do something or make something happen, esp. for a long time or against difficulties

name: avoid
trans: to stay away from someone or something, or prevent something from happening, or not allow yourself to do something

name: category
trans: a grouping of people or things by type in any systematic arrangement

name: destination
trans: the place where someone is going or where something is being sent or taken

name: wilderness
trans: an area of land that has not been farmed or had towns and roads built on it, esp. because it is difficult to live in as a result of its extremely cold or hot weather or bad earth

name: accommodations
trans: a place to stay, esp. a hotel room

name: recycling
trans: the process of collecting and changing old paper, glass, plastic, etc. so that it can be used again

name: barrier
trans: anything used or acting to block someone from going somewhere or from doing something, or to block something from happening

name: culprit
trans: someone who has committed a crime or done something wrong

name: dump
trans: to put down or drop something heavy without caring where it goes, or to get rid of something or someone no longer wanted

name: pleasure
trans: a feeling of enjoyment or satisfaction, or something that produces this feeling

name: remote
trans: far away in distance, time, or relation; not close

name: wary
trans: careful because you do not completely trust someone or something or are not certain about what you should do

name: principle
trans: a moral rule or standard of good behavior or fair dealing
